/-
We have formalized the definition of a regular prime and the Regular Prime Conjecture.
We have proven that 2 is a regular prime (`isRegularPrime_two`) by showing that the ring of integers of the 2nd cyclotomic field is isomorphic to ℤ, which is a PID.
This involved proving that the 2nd cyclotomic field is isomorphic to ℚ (`cyclotomicField_two_equiv_rat`) and that the property of being a principal ideal ring is preserved under ring equivalence (`isPrincipalIdealRing_of_ringEquiv`).
The Regular Prime Conjecture (`RegularPrimeConjecture`) is stated but remains unproven as it is an open problem.
-/

